are consuming

00:04:00.820 --> 00:04:02.930
YouTube content today.

00:04:02.930 --> 00:04:05.900
It's a huge audience, and
it continues to grow.

00:04:05.900 --> 00:04:07.040
And in fact, YouTube is now the

00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:09.680
third-largest site on the web.

00:04:09.680 --> 00:04:12.670
So think about, if your company
is not on YouTube,

00:04:12.670 --> 00:04:14.400
you're not on the third largest
site, you're not on

00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:16.180
the second-largest search
engine on the web.

00:04:18.800 --> 00:04:21.769
Beyond coming directly to the
site, when people watch

00:04:21.769 --> 00:04:23.360
YouTube videos, they
love to share them.

00:04:23.360 --> 00:04:26.240
This is very social content.

00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:29.290
And so, whether it's 700 videos
shared on Twitter every

00:04:29.290 --> 00:04:33.430
minute or on other social
platforms or people just

00:04:33.430 --> 00:04:38.110
emailing and sharing out links
in lots of different ways,

00:04:38.110 --> 00:04:40.980
this content is inherently
viral.

00:04:40.980 --> 00:04:44.800
And even if a consumer doesn't
have a habit of coming to

00:04:44.800 --> 00:04:46.940
YouTube each day-- like maybe
my mom, she's not a big

00:04:46.940 --> 00:04:47.995
YouTube user--

00:04:47.995 --> 00:04:50.570
I'm sending her videos all the
time, and she watches them,

00:04:50.570 --> 00:04:54.060
because I'm her son, and
I sent it to her.

00:04:54.060 --> 00:04:58.020
So YouTube is increasingly
getting in front of most of

00:04:58.020 --> 00:05:01.200
the consumers and the viewers
on the web, whether or not

00:05:01.200 --> 00:05:03.950
they come directly
to the site.

00:05:03.950 --> 00:05:06.860
