00:13:00.950 --> 00:13:03.010
audience thinks about your
product or service.

00:13:06.740 --> 00:13:09.276
So let's start with PR.

00:13:09.276 --> 00:13:13.100
The obvious first video for any
new company to create is a

00:13:13.100 --> 00:13:15.990
product video that explains
exactly what your product does

00:13:15.990 --> 00:13:18.130
and how it works.

00:13:18.130 --> 00:13:20.550
These product videos are really
great for you to share

00:13:20.550 --> 00:13:23.010
with any of the press or
bloggers that might be

00:13:23.010 --> 00:13:25.970
covering the launch of
your new product.

00:13:25.970 --> 00:13:28.500
The reason being is having a
video included in the blog

00:13:28.500 --> 00:13:32.360
post actually makes sure that
your message is clear and that

00:13:32.360 --> 00:13:36.920
none of the important features
or functionality is overlooked

00:13:36.920 --> 00:13:39.060
when the article is released.

00:13:39.060 --> 00:13:42.270
Because there's nothing more
frustrating than having your

00:13:42.270 --> 00:13:44.280
favorite feature not be
included when the

00:13:44.280 --> 00:13:46.720
news story comes out.

00:13:46.720 --> 00:13:51.900
So here's an example of a
company named CakeHealth that

00:13:51.900 --> 00:13:53.925
put together a great video
to be included in

00:13:53.925 --> 00:13:55.408
a TechCrunch article.

00:14:00.150 --> 00:14:03.040
So including the video in the
article is not only great for

00:14:03.040 --> 00:14:06.010
you, as the product owner, to
make sure that nothing gets

00:14:06.010 --> 00:14:08.480
lost, but it's also great
for the bloggers.

00:14:08.480 --> 00:14:11.420
So having a video makes it
really easy to make sure that

00:14:11.420 --> 00:14:13.550
your story's on point and that
you're not missing anything.

00:14:20.110 --> 00:14:22.710
So while the product videos
are great, you can't

00:14:22.710 --> 00:14:24.440
just stop at one.

00:14:24.440 --> 00:14:26.000
It's not a one-time thing.

00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:29.040
Instead, this should be an
ongoing thing as you develop

00:14:29.040 --> 00:14:30.380
new features.

00:14:30.380 --> 00:14:32.770
So this is especially important
for really complex

00:14:32.770 --> 00:14:39.100
products that are better said
broken into more digestible

00:14:39.100 --> 00:14:43.220
