00:37:20.250 --> 00:37:22.510
The other great product that we
have, that most people may

00:37:22.510 --> 00:37:25.200
not be familiar with, is
YouTube Analytics.

00:37:25.200 --> 00:37:28.190
So it's like Google Analytics,
but it's for the video content

00:37:28.190 --> 00:37:29.930
that you create.

00:37:29.930 --> 00:37:31.660
And there are a few things
that you can do

00:37:31.660 --> 00:37:33.160
with YouTube Analytics.

00:37:33.160 --> 00:37:36.670
The first is you can see where
your audience is coming from.

00:37:36.670 --> 00:37:39.150
So if you have videos on
YouTube, and people watch

00:37:39.150 --> 00:37:41.040
them, you can see what
cities and countries

00:37:41.040 --> 00:37:42.470
are they coming from.

00:37:42.470 --> 00:37:44.630
You can see what their
demographics are, in terms of

00:37:44.630 --> 00:37:45.880
age and gender.

00:37:48.800 --> 00:37:50.340
Just for example,
we have a lot of

00:37:50.340 --> 00:37:52.380
music artists on YouTube.

00:37:52.380 --> 00:37:53.540
And they put up their videos.

00:37:53.540 --> 00:37:56.830
And then they notice that their
music is being watched

00:37:56.830 --> 00:37:59.870
in countries like Sweden, even
though they've never marketed

00:37:59.870 --> 00:38:01.420
there, they've never
been there.

00:38:01.420 --> 00:38:04.110
And so we've heard of a lot of
cases where artists decide to

00:38:04.110 --> 00:38:06.920
go on tour and go visit some of
these communities, because

00:38:06.920 --> 00:38:08.680
they have found a
new audience.

00:38:08.680 --> 00:38:10.940
So a lot of you may be building
products, which you

00:38:10.940 --> 00:38:13.460
think are intended for the
US, but may have a

00:38:13.460 --> 00:38:14.920
great, global audience.

00:38:14.920 --> 00:38:16.990
And YouTube analytics can show
you exactly where your

00:38:16.990 --> 00:38:19.590
audience is coming from.

00:38:19.590 --> 00:38:23.090
Another great thing you can see
on Analytics is the source

00:38:23.090 --> 00:38:24.830
of traffic for your videos.

00:38:24.830 --> 00:38:27.070
So where are your videos
coming from?

00:38:27.070 --> 00:38:29.390
Are they all coming
from Search?

00:38:29.390 --> 00:38:31.980
Or are there certain sites or
other YouTube channels that

00:38:31.980 --> 00:38:33.570
are driving a lot of traffic?

00:38:33.570 --> 00:38:37.830
So if you remember back to
ijustine and TechnoBuffalo, if

00:38:37.830 --> 00:38:39.890
you see that some of these
channels are driving a lot of

00:38:39.890 --> 00:38:42.470
viewers to you, you probably
want to pick up the phone and

00:38:42.470 --> 00:38:44.560
get in touch with
these channels.

00:38:44.560 --> 00:38:45.810
They're sending you
a lot of traffic.

00:38:45.810 --> 00:38:48.490
You could probably deepen that
relationship and get even more

00:38:48.490 --> 00:38:51.010
love from them.

00:38:51.010 --> 00:38:52.900
The other thing you can do with
Analytics is you can look

00:38:52.900 --> 00:38:54.656
inside the video.

00:38:54.656 --> 00:38:57.400
And in this particular case, we
see a chart that shows the

00:38:57.400 --> 00:39:00.080
